CloudFront+WAF

  WAF Console → Web ACLs → Create Web ACL

Step 1 — Create WAF Web ACL:

AWS Console
→ WAF & Shield
→ Web ACLs
→ Create Web ACL
→ Name: my-waf
→ Region:       your region (or CloudFront global)
→ Associated resources:
    → Add your ALB / CloudFront / API Gateway here
→ Resource: CloudFront
→ Add rules:
   ✅ AWSManagedRulesCommonRuleSet
   ✅ AWSManagedRulesKnownBadInputsRuleSet
→ Create ✅

Step 2 — Attach WAF to CloudFront:

CloudFront Console
→ Your distribution (NLB origin)
→ Edit
→ Security tab
→ Web Application Firewall (WAF)
→ Enable security protections
→ Select your Web ACL: my-cloudfront-waf
→ Save changes ✅

Step 3 — Link WAF to Shield Advanced:

Shield Console
→ Protected Resources
→ Select your CloudFront
→ Associate WAF Web ACL
→ Select your WAF ✅
→ Save ✅

Without linking:
Shield blocks DDoS ──────────────────────→ independently
WAF blocks SQLi/XSS ─────────────────────→ independently

With linking:
Shield detects DDoS → automatically adds WAF rules → blocks faster ✅

Linking WAF to Shield Advanced is not mandatory since both work independently — but recommended for payment companies 
because it enables Shield to automatically create WAF rules during DDoS attacks and allows Shield Response Team to manage WAF rules for faster mitigation. ✅
